{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a59c1598-3abb-4cd4-82b4-3f3a4a3b2aa5",
    "name": "Law4Devs API",
    "description": "Structured EU regulatory compliance data for developers.\n\nAll 19 major EU digital regulations \u00e2\u20ac\u201d CRA, NIS2, DORA, GDPR, AI Act, eIDAS,\nDSA, DMA, Data Act, DGA, eIDAS2, CER, PSD2, MiCA, Cybersecurity Act,\nePrivacy, RED, CSRD, NIS1 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d parsed into structured articles, recitals,\nrequirements, compliance deadlines, and tags.\n\n## Response Conventions\n\n- **List responses** (paginated): `{ data: [...], meta: { api_version, total, page, per_page, pages }, links: { next, prev } }`\n- **List responses** (non-paginated): `{ data: [...], meta: { api_version, total } }`\n- **Detail responses**: `{ data: { ... } }`\n- **Error responses**: `{ error: { code: \"ERROR_CODE\", message: \"Human-readable message\" } }`\n\n## Pagination\n\nAll list endpoints accept `page` (\u00e2\u2030\u00a5 1, default 1) and `per_page` (1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c100, default 20).\nInvalid values return `400 INVALID_PARAM`.\n\nTotal endpoints: 22\n\n**Base URL:** `https://api.law4devs.eu/v1`\n\nImport the companion `law4devs.postman_environment.json` file, select the **Law4Devs \u2014 Production** environment, and set your `api_key` variable before sending requests.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      {
        "key": "key",
        "value": "X-API-Key",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "value",
        "value": "{{api_key}}",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "in",
        "value": "header",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "api_key",
      "value": "",
      "type": "secret",
      "description": "Your Law4Devs API key (sent as X-API-Key header)"
    }
  ],
